Params: {1: 'Assets/Product/Texture/Image/BgStory/BgStory14.png'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Duelist Construct', 3: 'I send Musashi V from my hand to the graveyard, activating its effect: Choose 1 Musashi card from your deck and place it into your hand.', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Duelist Construct', 3: 'And since I drew a Musashi card outside of my draw phase, I get to special summon Musashi Zero from my hand.', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Duelist Construct', 3: 'Once a Musashi Zero has been special summoned, I get to special summon another Musashi card from my hand.', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Rosetta', 3: "You're summoning two monsters at once...?!", 4: '2'}
{2: 'Duelist Construct', 3: "And the one I'm summoning is, of course, the one I added to my hand thanks to Musashi V—Musashi IX!", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Spectator A', 3: "Ooooh! He now has over 6,000 total monster damage! With no monsters on the field, Rosetta can't withstand the attack!", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Rosetta', 3: "Hmph, don't underestimate me. I activate my quick-attack card—Sky Striker Anchor!", 4: '2'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Duelist Construct', 3: 'N-nani?!', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Rosetta', 3: 'Sky Striker Anchor allows me to gain control of one monster on your field until the end of my turn. Which, of course, means your Musashi IX is mine!', 4: '2'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Spectator A', 3: "Oh, no! She took Musashi IX...?! It not only has an absurd attack of 3,100, it also can't be destroyed through combat!", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Spectator B', 3: 'Is Rosetta going to live through this round?', 4: '2'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Duelist Construct', 3: "Hmph, did you really think that I didn't see this coming?", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Spectator B', 3: 'Could it be...!', 4: '1'}
{1: 'RImgBg1Shake'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Duelist Construct', 3: 'I activate my trap card, Musashi Whirlwind!', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Duelist Construct', 3: "This card allows me to return any Musashi card on the battlefield to its owner's deck, and we each draw one card.", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Rosetta', 3: 'I get to draw one, too?', 4: '2'}
{2: 'Duelist Construct', 3: "Of course, but the card must also be revealed to all players! If it's a monster card, it can be directly summoned onto the battlefield!", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Spectator A', 3: 'Wait, but if Rosetta draws a monster card, then she might...', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Spectator B', 3: "No... With Rosetta's luck, she won't.", 4: '2'}
{2: 'Spectator A', 3: 'Is that how it works?!', 4: '1'}
{3: "On your way back to the Gray Raven's quarters, you hear fervent cheers coming from the engineering bay."}
{3: 'You decide to check out what all the fuss is about. As you enter the engineering bay, you see Rosetta and a Construct playing a card game.'}
{3: "From the looks of it, this round will likely be the final one, with this card draw deciding the players' fate."}
{3: 'Under the rambunctious cheering of less than ten spectators, the players place their hands on their decks.'}
{1: 'Assets/Product/Effect/Prefab/FxUi/FxUiStoryNew/FxUiStoryLineSpreadNew.prefab', 2: '3'}
{2: 'Duelist Construct', 3: 'Looks like Lady Luck is smiling upon me. I have drawn a monster card... Come forth, bearing the blade in your heart—Musashi IX!', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Assets/Product/Effect/Prefab/FxUi/FxUiStoryNew/FxUiStoryLineSpreadNew.prefab'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Spectator A', 3: 'I see! That must be why you slot three Musashi IXs into your deck!', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Spectator B', 3: "Um... I don't think that has anything to do with it.", 4: '2'}
{3: "Now clearly at a disadvantage, Rosetta's opponent and the crowd await her card draw in eager anticipation."}
{1: '1', 2: 'Rosetta', 3: "...It'd be nice if it were a monster card, but...", 4: '1'}
{3: 'Rosetta reveals the card she drew as a magic card. Her opponent leaps joyously into the air, and she lets out a sigh.'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Rosetta', 3: "It really isn't my lucky day.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Is the match over?', 3: '70', 4: "I didn't know you liked card games.", 5: '72'}
{2: 'Rosetta', 3: "Yeah, I lost. Looks like I'm no good at luck-based games.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Rosetta', 3: 'I guess I do, but I always lose.', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Rosetta', 3: 'Anyway... What brings you here, Commandant? Do you need something from the engineering bay?', 4: '1'}
{2: 'I came to see what the fuss was about.', 3: '76', 4: 'What are you doing here instead?', 5: '77'}
{2: 'Rosetta', 3: 'I see... Looks like we got carried away.', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Rosetta', 3: "Well, as you can see, I'm playing a card game. Before that, I was here for routine maintenance.", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Duelist Construct', 3: "Enough with the chit-chat, Rosetta. I'm sure you know what losing means!", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Rosetta', 3: "Yeah, I do... I'll be surveying the Arctic in your stead.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'You were deciding this over a duel?!', 3: '83'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Duelist Construct', 3: "It's a nonessential mission, and there's no time limit—that's why... Chill your beans, Gray Raven Commandant.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Duelist Construct', 3: "I'll send the mission details to your dedicated channel later. Rosetta, go register with our chief first.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Rosetta', 3: 'Uhm... But this mission requires at least two people...', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Rosetta', 3: "Will you go with me, Commandant? I know it's a bit out of the blue.", 4: '1'}
{2: "If it doesn't take too long, then sure.", 3: '91', 4: 'Okay.', 5: '92'}
{2: 'Rosetta', 3: "It shouldn't. The engineering staff said it's not high on the list of priorities.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Rosetta', 3: 'Thank you.', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Duelist Construct', 3: 'Got your team sorted? Just tell the chief Rosetta and the Gray Raven Commandant will be surveying the Arctic.', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Duelist Construct', 3: '...Hahahaha. With that mission sorted, I can spend time on assembling my hyper laser cannon instead!', 4: '1'}
{3: 'You leave before your mind gets further contaminated.'}
